16/01/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Federation of BiH Prime Minister Nedzad Brankovic confirmed on Tuesday (January 15th) that consultations are under way with the four ruling coalition parties on a possible cabinet reorganization. 
As they continue, he says he will assess the performance of each ministry and decide whether changes are in order. 
Local media reports suggest two people might be fired: Industry Minister Vahid Heco and Trade Minister Desnica Radivojevic. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 16/01/08; NTV Hayat - 15/01/08)
